# LAB 6: Smart RFID System with Cloud & SD Logging

## Overview

This project implements a smart RFID-based attendance system using ESP32 and MicroPython (Thonny). The system integrates an RFID-RC522 reader, SD card for local storage, Google Firestore for cloud logging, and a buzzer for real-time feedback. When a registered card is scanned, the system identifies the student, logs their attendance, and provides audio confirmation.

## Hardware Components

- ESP32 — Main microcontroller
- RFID-RC522 — Card reader (SPI interface)
- MicroSD Card Module — Local CSV data logging
- Buzzer — Audio feedback

## Wiring / Pin Configuration

### RFID-RC522 to ESP32

- 3.3V → 3.3V (do not use 5V)
- GND → GND
- RST → D22
- MISO → D19
- MOSI → D23
- SCK → D18
- SDA (CS) → D16

### SD Card Module to ESP32

- CS → D13
- SCK → D14
- MOSI → D15
- MISO → D2
- VCC → 5V
- GND → GND

### Buzzer to ESP32

- – (negative) → GND
- + (positive) → 5V
- S (signal) → D4

## System Flowchart

See `flowchart.png` for the full system flowchart diagram.

## Features

- Reads UID from RFID card via SPI
- Matches UID against a predefined student database
- Generates current datetime in `YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS` format
- Valid card: buzzer beeps for 0.3 seconds, logs data to SD card and Firestore
- Invalid card: buzzer beeps for 3 seconds, displays "Unknown Card" — no data saved

## Data Format

### CSV (SD Card) — `attendance.csv`

```
UID,Name,StudentID,Major,DateTime
A1B2C3D4,John Doe,20240001,Computer Engineering,2025-04-21 10:35:22
```

### Firestore Document Structure

```json
{
  "uid": "A1B2C3D4",
  "name": "John Doe",
  "student_id": "20240001",
  "major": "Computer Engineering",
  "datetime": "2025-04-21 10:35:22"
}
```

