## How to Run

1. Flash MicroPython firmware onto the ESP32.
2. Open Thonny IDE and connect to the ESP32 via serial port.
3. Upload `main.py` to the ESP32.
4. Ensure the SD card is formatted as FAT32 and inserted.
5. Configure your Wi-Fi credentials and Firestore API key in `main.py`.
6. Run `main.py` — the system will start scanning for RFID cards.

## Dependencies / Libraries

- `mfrc522` — MicroPython RFID-RC522 driver
- `sdcard` — MicroPython SD card driver
- `urequests` — HTTP requests for Firestore REST API
- `network` — Wi-Fi connection (built-in)
- `utime` / `ntptime` — Datetime generation (built-in)

